data.name: Nike Sportswear x Matt Stevens Present: #AIRMAX

Inspired by the exposed architecture of The Centre Pompidou in Paris, Tinker Hatfield revolutionized the game by turning things inside out and designing the first shoe with visible air, the Air Max 1.

When it debuted, the Air Max 90 sported the largest visible air bag to date. To draw attention to it, Tinker Hatfield placed the radiant red polyurethane around it and gave the shape movement. Designed to look as fast as it performed.  The 90 was unmistakably about one thing: speed.
Inspired by the human anatomy, designer Sergio Lozano modeled the the Air Max 95's sole after the spine, the lace straps: ribs, the gradient upper: muscle fibers, and the mesh: skin.
The Air Max 97. Sleek and silver. Just like the Japanese high speed train that inspired its unique design.

In 1987, sneakers were either white or grey. Never one to conform, Tinker Hatfield grabbed the brightest marker he had and gave the Air Max 1 its signature red. Little did he know how that would change the game.

data.message: I feel so honored to be the first comment. All of my hard-working dedication paid off. Getting the top comment has been a dream of mine for many years, and I would like to thank all of those would've helped me along the way. First and foremost I would like to thank God for giving me this opportunity. Next I would like to thank my parents. I would like to thank my cat Espresso, for being fat and their for me. I would also like to thank my pet tadpole for surviving against all odds for over a week. Next I would like to thank the squirrel my backyard for climbing trees because that gives me the inspiration I need to get through the day. This is a special moment in my life and I would like to thank any unmentioned friends and family that have helped me along the way. This moment will be a moment I will never forget. I just remembered a few other people I would like to thank; Facebook, the fish I caught in third grade, my light in my room because I wouldn't be able to see the keyboard without it, the Internet for letting me go on Facebook, my house because without it I would be homeless, and last but not least I would like to thank the people that actually took time out of their day to read this. I cannot stress how much of a big deal this is to me. I have been trying to be the first comment on a post for years, but that has not been possible until this amazing day. Hopefully my luck will continue, but this is undoubtedly a rare occasion. If you asked me how I did this, I would say, you can achieve anything if you set your mind to it. To all the kids out there reading this, I would like to tell them to follow their dreams. Being the top comment is amazing, thank you everyone.
